It's time to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house where, apart from a bit of decorating, nothing else has been done.
The disgusting electric fireplace and the hearth must go. We need to surround the fireplace, replace and smooth out the loose plaster, and then build a custom wardrobe.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch…
The dirty part of the job is done.
At the back of the chimney, we found a few dead birds, very dry :(
Alles ready for the plasterer next week
The small side niche turned out great
Here comes a new closet in (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought of installing this nice little vent flap so the chimney doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the covering and chimney pot. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens who like to nest up there 🪺
The plasterer is finished. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlayment is in place, I've cobbled together a sawdust-extractor for the vacuum cleaner out of a toilet paper roll 😂
The parts for the floor are finished and can be laid. We're taking a tea break right now
Ugh. Today's progress is slow due to super complicated cuts around the doorposts, so we can have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be newly laid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
Fertig, but at the end! The crowning glory was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
Still missing: the floor in the hallway and all the baseboards. The interior designer is coming in a month, so we have DIY chic for the time being.
Some more DIY work in the evening to saw or file the lower sections around the doorposts so the floor will fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlayment is now also in the hallway.
We finished the floor in the hallway yesterday! Then out at 5 am to pick up item 1 at Heathrow, then a snooze and a final push in the hallway, the baseboards are in place. The joints will be made when the adhesive is dry.
